description: The world bought 928 billion face masks at a cost of $389 billion during the COVID-19 pandemic from 2020 to 2022, according to data from Statista.

title: Michigan state police bust California driver with enough deadly drug to kill about one-third of the state
description: Michigan State Police (MSP) arrested a California driver on Tuesday after pulling over his vehicle and seizing enough fentanyl to kill three million people potentially.

title: Massive 11-foot, 1,200-pound great white shark detected off Florida coast as spring breakers flock to beaches
description: An 11-foot, 1,264 pounds great white shark pinged off of Florida's Gulf Coast on Monday ahead of spring break for college student's across America.

title: Michael J. Fox cuddles new puppy in adorable photo
description: Michael J. Fox is sharing an adorable picture with his new puppy, Blue. The latest addition comes after the "Back to the Future" star's dog Gus died in April 2021.

title: Pennsylvania Gov. Shapiro's picks for AG, State Police chief confirmed unanimously
description: The Pennsylvania Senate confirmed Michelle Henry and Christopher Paris, nominated by Democratic Gov. Josh Shapiro to become Attorney General and State Police chief, respectively.

title: 2 boys shot, 1 fatally, after stray bullet enters Las Vegas apartment
description: Two young boys were shot after a stray bullet entered their Las Vegas apartment. One of the boys died, and the other is being treated for his injuries.

title: Miami-Dade officer 'ambushed,' shot by 'cowardly' suspect, Florida officials say
description: A Miami-Dade police officer was shot from behind Wednesday while working a drug case, authorities in Florida said. The gunman was being sought.

title: ESPN issues public apology after Kendrick Perkins claimed NBA MVP voters were predominantly white
description: ESPN issued an apology on "First Take" Wednesday morning for Kendrick Perkins' claim that 80% of NBA MVP voters were white, saying it was a fact during an argument.

title: Kevin McCarthy and Hakeem Jeffries demand answers on 'significant' data breach affecting members and staff
description: House Speaker Kevin McCarthy and Minority Leader Hakeem Jeffries sent a joint letter Wednesday demanding answers about the “significant data breach" of DC Health Link.

title: Kentucky teen's murder solved after nearly half a century
description: The Boone County Sheriff's Office in Kentucky used advanced DNA technology to solve the cold case murder of a 16-year-old girl in 1976.

title: Site of Rochester, New York, concert stampede loses entertainment license
description: Rochester, New York's Main Street Armory has lost its entertainment license following a deadly stampede at a concert headlined by rapper GloRilla.

title: Local media cut feed on DeSantis' 'book ban hoax' stream due to 'explicit content'
description: Media outlets cut the live feed to Gov. Ron DeSantis’, R-Fla., video presentation on the books banned in Florida schools on Wednesday, citing “explicit” content.

title: Senate Dems overwhelmingly vote with GOP to overturn controversial DC crime law
description: The Senate was widely expected to approve the resolution to block DC's crime bill after Biden said he would not veto it if it came to his desk

title: UPS must pay Missouri family $75M after driver struck pregnant woman's car
description: A jury decided that UPS must pay a Missouri family after one of their drivers collided with a pregnant woman's car. The woman's baby was later born with brain damage.

title: GOP, Dems team up to kill Gaetz resolution removing US troops from Syria
description: A majority of House Republicans and Democrats voted down a resolution from Rep. Matt Gaetz calling for the removal of U.S. troops from Syria.

title: Former North Carolina congressional candidate pleads guilty to campaign finance violation
description: A former North Carolina congressional candidate pleaded guilty to a federal campaign finance violation. The ex-candidate accepted a loan that prosecutors said was falsely recorded in reports.

title: Alabama’s Nick Saban talks NIL, says recruits are choosing to play ‘where they can make the most money’
description: Alabama head football coach Nick Saban discussed name, image and likeness, saying athletes are choosing schools based on where they can make the most money.

title: Universal theme parks division gets new name in rebranding
description: The Universal theme parks division will be changing their name during rebranding to Universal Destinations & Experiences. Officials believe this change will better reflect the parks.

title: Montana officer, suspect seriously injured in shooting
description: A Montana officer and a suspect were seriously injured in a shooting following a traffic altercation. The occupants of the vehicle got out and tried to flee after being pulled over.

title: GOP senator snaps at union boss during heated hearing: 'Shut your mouth'
description: Republican Oklahoma Sen. Markwayne Mullin snapped on Teamster President Sean O'Brien during a heated Senate committee hearing on Wednesday.

title: Historic 160-year-old church in New York listed for sale at 'cheap price' of $100K: See the stunning images
description: St. Joseph's Church in Albany, New York's Arbor Hill neighborhood, has been listed for sale. The historic building closed in the 1990s; the city hopes a buyer will restore it.
